Interface ParticipantAudio

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Observable, ParticipantService

    public interface ParticipantAudio
extends ParticipantService
    This interface represents the audio capabilities of a participant in the conversation.

      • PARTICIPANT_IS_SPEAKING_PROPERTY_ID

        static final int PARTICIPANT_IS_SPEAKING_PROPERTY_ID
        Property ID for notifying that there is a change in the speaking action for the participant. Subscribers will be notified via the onPropertyChanged method on the Observable.OnPropertyChangedCallback interface with this property id. E.g. callback.onPropertyChanged(PARTICIPANT_IS_SPEAKING_PROPERTY_ID). Clients are expected to call the isSpeaking method in the callback to get the changed state.

      • setMuted

        void setMuted(boolean mute)
       throws SFBException
        Controls whether this participant's audio can be heard by other participants in the conversation. This action may may not be available if the local participant does not have the 'leader' role in the conversation. To toggle the mute state of the local participant please use (AudioService.toggleMute()) (Conversation.getSelfParticipant()). In particular, it may not always be possible to un-mute until a remote 'leader' enables this.
        Parameters:
        mute - true - mute, false - un-mute.
        Throws:
        SFBException - SFBException object.

      • canSetMuted

        boolean canSetMuted()
        Checks if the participant can be muted / un-muted. As per (setMuted(boolean)) a number of different factors may determine this.
        Returns:
        boolean true if the mute / un-mute property can be set, false otherwise.
